From: larsoft conda packaging
Subject: [PATCH] find_package(Eigen3): force CONFIG mode, drop the 3.3 version bound

lareventdisplay's 3DDrawers/SimDrawers art plugins link Eigen3::Eigen (PRIVATE),
which is provided by the top-level `find_package(Eigen3 3.3 REQUIRED)`. That call is
fragile against the conda stack:

  * cetmodules ships share/cetmodules/Modules/FindEigen3.cmake (MODULE mode). It only
    creates the Eigen3::Eigen target by internally running `find_package(Eigen3
    CONFIG)` under `if (NOT Eigen3_FOUND)`. If Eigen3_FOUND is already set (e.g. by a
    transitive find, or a stale CMakeCache), that config find is skipped and no
    target is created.
  * conda-forge's eigen is 5.0.1, whose Eigen3ConfigVersion.cmake treats a "3.3"
    request as the range [3.3, 3.4) and reports 5.0.1 as INCOMPATIBLE. So a plain
    CONFIG-mode resolution of `Eigen3 3.3` is rejected outright.

In both failure modes find_package "succeeds" (or is bypassed) without defining
Eigen3::Eigen, and the plugins then fail at generate time with
"Target ... links to: Eigen3::Eigen but the target was not found".

Fix: resolve Eigen in CONFIG mode with no version bound. CONFIG bypasses cetmodules'
module and its Eigen3_FOUND guard and includes Eigen3Config.cmake directly (which does
`if (NOT TARGET Eigen3::Eigen) include(Eigen3Targets.cmake)`), always defining the
target; dropping the version avoids eigen 5.0.1's range rejection. Eigen is header-only
and neither larsoft nor its consumers require exactly 3.3.

--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -42,7 +42,14 @@
 find_package(nuevdb REQUIRED EXPORT)
 find_package(nusimdata REQUIRED EXPORT)

-find_package(Eigen3 3.3 REQUIRED)
+# Force CONFIG mode and drop the version bound. cetmodules' FindEigen3.cmake
+# (MODULE mode) only creates the Eigen3::Eigen target when it can run
+# find_package(Eigen3 CONFIG); a pre-set Eigen3_FOUND short-circuits that, and
+# eigen 5.0.1's ConfigVersion rejects a "3.3" request (treats it as [3.3,3.4)),
+# so in either case Eigen3::Eigen is never defined and the PRIVATE-linked drawer
+# plugins fail with 'target Eigen3::Eigen not found'. Going straight to CONFIG
+# with no version always includes Eigen3Config.cmake, which defines the target.
+find_package(Eigen3 REQUIRED CONFIG)
 find_package(ROOT COMPONENTS Core EG Geom Gpad Gui Hist MathCore REQUIRED EXPORT)

 # macros for dictionary and simple_plugin
